# Kimigayo OS License Information

Kimigayo OS is a Linux distribution composed of various software components,
each with its own license. This file provides an overview of the licensing
structure, following the approach of Alpine Linux.

## License Overview

Kimigayo OS follows Alpine Linux's licensing philosophy: each component
maintains its original license, and we clearly document all licenses used.

## Component Licenses

### Core Operating System Components

| Component | License | Location |
|-----------|---------|----------|
| Linux Kernel | GPL-2.0 | LICENSES/GPL-2.0.txt |
| musl libc | MIT | LICENSES/MIT.txt |
| BusyBox | GPL-2.0 | LICENSES/GPL-2.0.txt |
| OpenRC (Init System) | BSD-2-Clause | LICENSES/BSD-2-Clause.txt |

### Kimigayo OS Original Components

| Component | License | Location |
|-----------|---------|----------|
| isn (Package Manager) | MIT | LICENSES/MIT.txt |
| Build System | MIT | LICENSES/MIT.txt |
| Documentation | MIT | LICENSES/MIT.txt |
| Test Framework | MIT | LICENSES/MIT.txt |

## Directory-Specific Licenses

```
src/
├── kernel/        # GPL-2.0 (Linux Kernel configurations)
├── init/          # BSD-2-Clause (OpenRC-based)
├── pkg/           # MIT (isn - original implementation)
├── utils/         # GPL-2.0 (BusyBox configurations)
└── build/         # MIT (Build utilities)

tests/             # MIT
scripts/           # MIT
docs/              # MIT
```

## Third-Party Components

When you install packages using `isn`, each package maintains its own
license. You can check package licenses using:

```bash
isn info <package-name>
```

## License Identification

Kimigayo OS uses SPDX short identifiers for license identification,
following Alpine Linux's convention.

Common SPDX identifiers used:
- GPL-2.0: GNU General Public License v2.0
- MIT: MIT License
- BSD-2-Clause: BSD 2-Clause "Simplified" License

## Compliance

### Using Kimigayo OS

You are free to:
- Use Kimigayo OS for any purpose (commercial or non-commercial)
- Modify and distribute Kimigayo OS
- Create derivative works

Subject to the terms of the individual component licenses.

### Contributing to Kimigayo OS

By contributing to Kimigayo OS, you agree that:
- Your contributions to original components (build system, isn, etc.) will be licensed under MIT
- Your contributions to existing components will be licensed under their respective licenses
- You have the right to submit the contributions under these licenses

## Full License Texts

Full license texts are available in the `LICENSES/` directory:
- `LICENSES/GPL-2.0.txt` - GNU General Public License v2.0
- `LICENSES/MIT.txt` - MIT License
- `LICENSES/BSD-2-Clause.txt` - BSD 2-Clause License

## Additional Information

For complete license texts and more information:
- GPL-2.0: https://www.gnu.org/licenses/old-licenses/gpl-2.0.html
- MIT: https://opensource.org/licenses/MIT
- BSD-2-Clause: https://opensource.org/licenses/BSD-2-Clause

